<subSubSection pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="463">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="463">Note:</emphasis>
Melzheimer (in Rechinger, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="463">Fl. Iranica</emphasis>
163: 499. 1988) stated 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Typus…">&quot;Typus...</normalizedToken>
Herb. Linn.&quot;, but this does not distinguish between sheets 582.8 and 582.10, both of which bear the epithet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“aegyptiacus”">&quot;aegyptiacus&quot;</normalizedToken>
. However, on sheet 582.8 this epithet has been deleted in favour of &quot;5 stellatus&quot; (written by Linnaeus), and the material is a good match for the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cucubalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="463">C. stellatus</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, of which name it is the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
. Sheet 582.10 bears material received from Latour, lacks a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="463">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“7”">&quot;7&quot;</normalizedToken>
), and was received after 1753. Neither sheet is original material for 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="463">
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1753" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cucubalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">C. aegyptiacus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Linnaeus mentioned Hasselquist in the protologue but, in the absence of any extant material, Hosny designated a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
